1
00:00:07,721 --> 00:00:09,481
[If you don't turn yourself in,
your limbs will rot and you'll die]

2
00:00:37,938 --> 00:00:41,368
[All characters and events are fictional,
and any resemblance is coincidental]

3
00:00:41,368 --> 00:00:44,038
[Scenes with children and animals were filmed
safely under professional supervision]

4
00:00:55,305 --> 00:00:57,205
Lee Yong Woo!

5
00:00:57,205 --> 00:01:02,338
It seems like you've always been cheered on
whenever you open your mouth.

6
00:01:02,338 --> 00:01:03,972
But this place is different.

7
00:01:03,972 --> 00:01:08,772
This isn't a place where we blindly believe
whatever criminals say.

8
00:01:10,738 --> 00:01:12,905
<i>If this were the old days,</i>

9
00:01:12,905 --> 00:01:15,872
<i>I would've already
had my hands around her neck.</i>

10
00:01:26,272 --> 00:01:30,305
<i>Don't serial killers do that kind of thing?</i>

11
00:01:30,972 --> 00:01:34,005
<i>Competing over who killed more,</i>

12
00:01:34,905 --> 00:01:36,805
<i>ranking themselves</i>

13
00:01:36,805 --> 00:01:38,805
like it's a contest.

14
00:02:10,738 --> 00:02:15,405
That darn prosecutor thinks
I'm all talk, you know?

15
00:02:15,405 --> 00:02:19,172
She kept asking over and over
whether the 7th case was really my doing!

16
00:02:20,038 --> 00:02:24,372
She must have thought you were lying
because of your need to show off.

17
00:02:24,372 --> 00:02:26,572
Show off? Me?

18
00:02:26,572 --> 00:02:29,769
There actually have been cases
like that among serial killers.

19
00:02:29,769 --> 00:02:31,505
Jeez!

20
00:02:32,705 --> 00:02:33,838
Tae Joo.

21
00:02:33,838 --> 00:02:37,972
If even the prosecutor doesn't believe me,
how can I expect anyone else to?

22
00:02:37,972 --> 00:02:40,038
So, the thing is,

23
00:02:40,038 --> 00:02:42,638
how do I make people believe me?

24
00:02:44,238 --> 00:02:45,938
Do you think you'll get that chance?

25
00:02:45,938 --> 00:02:48,472
The prosecution questioning is over,
and now there's no more...

26
00:02:48,472 --> 00:02:50,538
Court! The courtroom!

27
00:02:50,538 --> 00:02:53,105
Yeah, the Seok Man case.

28
00:02:53,105 --> 00:02:55,772
I'll testify as a witness in the retrial.

29
00:02:55,772 --> 00:02:57,572
That is enough, right?

30
00:02:57,572 --> 00:02:59,805
So tell me quickly

31
00:02:59,805 --> 00:03:02,438
what I'm supposed to say.

32
00:03:07,505 --> 00:03:09,605
So the Seok Man case,

33
00:03:10,405 --> 00:03:13,205
I'll testify, but there's a condition.

34
00:03:13,205 --> 00:03:15,238
What kind of condition?

35
00:03:15,238 --> 00:03:17,972
Wasn't testifying in court
meant to be for you?

36
00:03:17,972 --> 00:03:19,972
You said you wanted to show people
who you are.

37
00:03:19,972 --> 00:03:21,438
Yeah, I did.

38
00:03:21,438 --> 00:03:24,305
But I changed my mind.

39
00:03:25,805 --> 00:03:27,805
What's your condition?

40
00:03:32,372 --> 00:03:34,072
My nephew.

41
00:03:35,138 --> 00:03:37,338
I want to meet him.

42
00:03:39,172 --> 00:03:40,838
What?

43
00:03:49,438 --> 00:03:52,872
[Muwon District Court
Episode 12]

44
00:03:52,872 --> 00:03:57,005
I was dragged in and couldn't sleep for days.

45
00:03:58,105 --> 00:04:00,972
They wouldn't let me sleep until I confessed.

46
00:04:01,672 --> 00:04:05,972
When I refused to write a statement,
they even kicked my chair.

47
00:04:05,972 --> 00:04:11,338
As you can see, even though I have a limp,
they still made me do jumping jacks.

48
00:04:11,338 --> 00:04:14,405
Are you saying there was abuse
during the interrogation?

49
00:04:14,405 --> 00:04:15,472
Yes.

50
00:04:15,472 --> 00:04:18,605
[Witness Stand]
That is not true.

51
00:04:18,605 --> 00:04:23,505
At the time, a suspect had died
due to alleged abuse,

52
00:04:23,505 --> 00:04:25,805
so everyone was being very careful.

53
00:04:25,805 --> 00:04:29,638
Above all, I don't know how to write.

54
00:04:29,638 --> 00:04:32,505
Then how did you end up writing a statement?

55
00:04:32,505 --> 00:04:35,338
They gave me a pre-written document
and told me to copy it.

56
00:04:35,338 --> 00:04:41,905
But that was based on transcribing
Im Seok Man's recorded testimony.

57
00:04:43,238 --> 00:04:47,705
We tried our best
to make things easy for him.

58
00:04:49,972 --> 00:04:53,505
At the time, I didn't
participate in the interrogation,

59
00:04:53,505 --> 00:04:57,038
but I saw Im Seok Man
being moved around several times.

60
00:04:57,038 --> 00:05:00,405
As far as I remember, I don't recall
seeing any signs of assault.

61
00:05:00,405 --> 00:05:03,838
And at that time, the evidence was so solid

62
00:05:03,838 --> 00:05:06,672
that there was no need for extreme measures.

63
00:05:06,672 --> 00:05:09,038
What sort of evidence was it?

64
00:05:09,038 --> 00:05:12,072
Hair from the perpetrator
was found at the scene,

65
00:05:12,072 --> 00:05:15,305
and tests showed it belonged to Im Seok Man.

66
00:05:15,305 --> 00:05:18,005
What sort of test was that?

67
00:05:18,005 --> 00:05:21,038
It was a radioactive isotope test.

68
00:05:21,038 --> 00:05:25,572
Then who requested this test?

69
00:05:25,572 --> 00:05:28,272
It was my misjudgment.

70
00:05:28,272 --> 00:05:31,072
What exactly was the mistake?

71
00:05:31,072 --> 00:05:32,972
This is not a test

72
00:05:32,972 --> 00:05:36,338
that can identify a criminal
like DNA analysis.

73
00:05:36,338 --> 00:05:41,138
At best, we can only find out
about the perpetrator's living environment.

74
00:05:41,138 --> 00:05:46,938
So you're saying there's no direct evidence
that the defendant is the real killer?

75
00:05:46,938 --> 00:05:48,738
Yes, that's correct.

76
00:05:49,705 --> 00:05:52,005
As a police officer,

77
00:05:52,005 --> 00:05:55,272
I acknowledge my mistake

78
00:05:55,272 --> 00:05:57,005
in judgment.

79
00:06:00,272 --> 00:06:02,172
I would like

80
00:06:05,638 --> 00:06:07,738
to take this opportunity
to sincerely apologize

81
00:06:08,405 --> 00:06:10,972
to Mr. Im Seok Man.

82
00:06:27,405 --> 00:06:29,672
Just one more thing, if I may.

83
00:06:29,672 --> 00:06:34,805
Do you believe the defendant's claim
that there was abuse during interrogation?

84
00:06:34,805 --> 00:06:36,738
Yes, I do.

85
00:06:36,738 --> 00:06:38,472
How can you be so certain?

86
00:06:38,472 --> 00:06:41,338
At the time, you did not
witness the interrogation.

87
00:06:41,338 --> 00:06:46,638
Because there had been a previous suspect
who was tortured during interrogation.

88
00:06:46,638 --> 00:06:48,605
Who was that?

89
00:06:48,605 --> 00:06:52,705
It's Lee Seong Jin, who was
being investigated as a suspect

90
00:06:54,338 --> 00:06:56,405
in the Kangseng Serial Murder Case back then.

91
00:07:01,305 --> 00:07:03,072
- Sir!
- Jeez!

92
00:07:03,072 --> 00:07:06,072
Please save me! I'm really innocent!

93
00:07:12,905 --> 00:07:14,005
Your Honor,

94
00:07:14,005 --> 00:07:16,805
I request Lee Seong Jin as a court witness.

95
00:07:16,805 --> 00:07:18,665
[Judge's Bench]

96
00:07:21,353 --> 00:07:22,938
[Witness Stand]
Yes.

97
00:07:22,938 --> 00:07:24,838
I was tortured

98
00:07:24,838 --> 00:07:27,272
by the police.

99
00:07:27,272 --> 00:07:32,205
Are the officers who tortured you
present in this courtroom, Mr. Lee Seong Jin?

100
00:07:33,438 --> 00:07:35,072
Yes.

101
00:07:40,272 --> 00:07:44,272
Who are they? Can you point them out?

102
00:07:56,472 --> 00:07:58,472
Jang Myeong Do.

103
00:07:59,272 --> 00:08:01,172
Do Hyeong Gu.

104
00:08:04,605 --> 00:08:06,705
Those are the ones.

105
00:08:17,438 --> 00:08:19,205
That is all.

106
00:08:20,238 --> 00:08:23,705
Your Honor, just because
the witness went through that

107
00:08:23,705 --> 00:08:26,472
doesn't mean the defendant also did.

108
00:08:26,472 --> 00:08:28,905
The witness was also investigated
in the same case

109
00:08:28,905 --> 00:08:31,505
and even confessed despite being innocent.

110
00:08:31,505 --> 00:08:33,772
[Witness Stand]
It's no different from the defendant's case.

111
00:08:33,772 --> 00:08:38,272
If violence was inflicted on the witness,
could the defendant really have avoided it?

112
00:08:38,272 --> 00:08:39,738
Your Honor.

113
00:08:39,738 --> 00:08:43,405
The witness' case can
serve as grounds for reasonable doubt.

114
00:08:46,738 --> 00:08:48,505
Sustained.

115
00:09:00,772 --> 00:09:02,372
Excuse me.

116
00:09:05,705 --> 00:09:07,705
Hello,

117
00:09:07,705 --> 00:09:10,438
I'm Reporter Cha Young Beom of Noise Cut.

118
00:09:14,438 --> 00:09:17,505
I don't do interviews.

119
00:09:20,638 --> 00:09:23,138
My father was also subjected to torture.

120
00:09:29,372 --> 00:09:31,805
He eventually died because of it.

121
00:09:34,672 --> 00:09:37,238
I... I'm sorry for your loss.

122
00:09:39,138 --> 00:09:42,005
What would you like to ask me?

123
00:09:43,705 --> 00:09:46,305
Were Jang Myeong Do and Do Hyeong Gu

124
00:09:46,305 --> 00:09:49,372
the only ones who assaulted you back then?

125
00:09:50,305 --> 00:09:52,372
What about Detective Kang Tae Joo?

126
00:09:53,905 --> 00:09:58,972
He is the one who released me, my savior.

127
00:09:58,972 --> 00:10:01,438
If it weren't for him...

128
00:10:09,472 --> 00:10:11,369
I would've

129
00:10:11,369 --> 00:10:15,572
confessed like that man earlier too,

130
00:10:17,505 --> 00:10:21,705
after being pressured by that prosecutor.

131
00:10:21,705 --> 00:10:23,605
Which prosecutor are you talking about?

132
00:10:23,605 --> 00:10:25,438
Cha Si Young.

133
00:10:26,138 --> 00:10:28,338
Prosecutor Cha Si Young.

134
00:10:28,338 --> 00:10:33,338
I can never forget that name.

135
00:10:40,405 --> 00:10:43,438
Today, Mr. Lee Seong Jin's testimony
was very helpful.

136
00:10:43,438 --> 00:10:46,872
Please tell him I'm grateful.

137
00:10:49,172 --> 00:10:52,672
I'll try to persuade Lee Yong Woo myself.

138
00:10:52,672 --> 00:10:57,205
Yes, then why don't you come
to my office with me, sir?

139
00:11:12,538 --> 00:11:14,605
Hey, Kang Tae Joo.

140
00:11:17,638 --> 00:11:20,272
Has it been 31 years?

141
00:11:29,538 --> 00:11:33,038
When I first saw you on TV,

142
00:11:34,138 --> 00:11:36,838
I felt a bit hurt.

143
00:11:36,838 --> 00:11:40,638
I thought you'd at least come
see me when you came back.

144
00:11:40,638 --> 00:11:41,929
Well,

145
00:11:41,929 --> 00:11:44,572
it wasn't as easy as I thought.

146
00:11:46,572 --> 00:11:49,672
I actually like seeing you on TV.

147
00:11:49,672 --> 00:11:52,805
I've been keeping up with all your reports.

148
00:11:52,805 --> 00:11:55,372
You're still the Seo Ji Won I knew.

149
00:11:55,372 --> 00:11:58,938
- Still so cool.
- Cool, my foot.

150
00:11:58,938 --> 00:12:04,638
If that's the case, you should've
come directly. Why send a tip?

151
00:12:04,638 --> 00:12:07,705
"Scarecrow1988."

152
00:12:07,705 --> 00:12:09,238
Huh?

153
00:12:09,238 --> 00:12:11,305
Seriously,

154
00:12:11,305 --> 00:12:14,472
I totally knew it was you
the moment I saw the ID.

155
00:12:14,472 --> 00:12:16,172
Jeez.

156
00:12:16,172 --> 00:12:18,972
So you knew about Hye Jin's case

157
00:12:18,972 --> 00:12:22,338
even 30 years ago?

158
00:12:24,972 --> 00:12:27,753
And you stayed silent

159
00:12:27,753 --> 00:12:29,205
because of Sun Young?

160
00:12:29,205 --> 00:12:31,849
They told me I had to leave Kangseng

161
00:12:31,849 --> 00:12:34,205
to save Sun Young.

162
00:12:34,857 --> 00:12:36,937
Jeez.

163
00:12:37,938 --> 00:12:41,905
So that's why you left. That's why...

164
00:12:44,873 --> 00:12:47,017
Oh, my.

165
00:12:47,838 --> 00:12:50,605
Why didn't you say anything?

166
00:12:50,605 --> 00:12:53,005
- If I had known...
- If you had known,

167
00:12:53,005 --> 00:12:55,805
do you think you would've stayed quiet?

168
00:12:56,638 --> 00:13:00,605
You would've tried to dig into
Hye Jin's case no matter what, right?

169
00:13:00,605 --> 00:13:03,438
And you would've been in danger too.

170
00:13:03,438 --> 00:13:05,188
I...

171
00:13:05,188 --> 00:13:06,938
I didn't know any of that,

172
00:13:06,938 --> 00:13:08,329
so...

173
00:13:08,329 --> 00:13:12,205
I just thought you'd left so irresponsibly

174
00:13:12,205 --> 00:13:14,405
and resented you for it.

175
00:13:19,605 --> 00:13:22,805
Whatever the reason,
it was still irresponsible.

176
00:13:22,805 --> 00:13:26,505
I stayed silent for 30 years
because of a promise

177
00:13:26,505 --> 00:13:29,072
made with my sister's life as collateral.

178
00:13:29,938 --> 00:13:33,305
For far longer than
the statute of limitations.

179
00:13:34,872 --> 00:13:37,105
It's late,

180
00:13:37,105 --> 00:13:40,338
but I'm going to fix

181
00:13:40,338 --> 00:13:42,505
everything I ruined.

182
00:13:45,272 --> 00:13:47,872
Yeah, I can't stay still, either.

183
00:13:47,872 --> 00:13:50,405
Let's do it together.

184
00:13:50,405 --> 00:13:52,138
- Alright.
- Alright.

185
00:13:54,472 --> 00:13:57,705
By the way, I'm worried about
Sun Young and Young Beom.

186
00:13:57,705 --> 00:14:03,638
They'll be deeply hurt if they find out
what Cha Si Young did, right?

187
00:14:04,705 --> 00:14:08,238
I don't intend to let Young Beom
find out what happened to his father.

188
00:14:08,238 --> 00:14:09,513
But still,

189
00:14:09,513 --> 00:14:14,272
they should know about
the Im Seok Man and Yoon Hye Jin cases.

190
00:14:25,105 --> 00:14:27,209
[The end of the Kangseng Serial
Murder Case is in sight]

191
00:14:28,305 --> 00:14:32,038
<i>For the arrest of the Kangseng
serial murder suspect Im,</i>

192
00:14:32,038 --> 00:14:36,772
<i>commendations were awarded
to four police officers and one prosecutor.</i>

193
00:14:36,772 --> 00:14:40,072
<i>Among the recipients were
Superintendent Cha Jun Young...</i>

194
00:14:40,072 --> 00:14:41,905
My eldest uncle?

195
00:14:44,438 --> 00:14:45,993
<i>Sergeant Jang Myeong Do,</i>

196
00:14:45,993 --> 00:14:49,505
<i>Sergeant Do Hyeong Gu,
Corporal Park Dae Ho, and...</i>

197
00:14:51,305 --> 00:14:53,105
Prosecutor Cha Si Young.

198
00:15:02,405 --> 00:15:06,138
<i>So both of my uncles
were rewarded for that case?</i>

199
00:15:07,438 --> 00:15:08,938
Mr. Cha.

200
00:15:08,938 --> 00:15:12,105
Once this is all printed out,
bring it to the conference room, please.

201
00:15:12,105 --> 00:15:13,805
Oh, okay.

202
00:15:14,537 --> 00:15:16,617
[Copying]

203
00:15:24,038 --> 00:15:26,857
[Searching for the Missing,
Name: Yoon Hye Jin]

204
00:15:30,205 --> 00:15:34,605
But how could the police possibly bury
a child's body and cover up a case like that?

205
00:15:34,605 --> 00:15:37,572
I couldn't believe it at first, either.

206
00:15:37,572 --> 00:15:40,805
Yoon Hye Jin went missing
right after Im Seok Man was arrested.

207
00:15:40,805 --> 00:15:44,072
Back then, Kangseng Station was
celebrating the capture of a serial killer.

208
00:15:44,072 --> 00:15:47,472
So when another body was found,
they probably wanted to cover it up.

209
00:15:47,472 --> 00:15:48,472
Even if it meant burying it.

210
00:15:48,472 --> 00:15:50,872
Who among the police could have done that?

211
00:15:50,872 --> 00:15:55,138
We need at least a rough suspect, so we can
start an investigation and prevent rumors.

212
00:15:55,138 --> 00:15:58,172
Those who would be in trouble
if another serial murder happened.

213
00:15:58,172 --> 00:16:01,072
It would be the ones who received awards
for arresting Im Seok Man, right?

214
00:16:01,072 --> 00:16:03,705
We should first figure out who they are.

215
00:16:05,372 --> 00:16:07,772
Corporal Park Dae Ho.

216
00:16:07,772 --> 00:16:09,417
Sergeant Do Hyeong Gu,

217
00:16:09,417 --> 00:16:12,538
Sergeant Jang Myeong Do,
Superintendent Cha Jun Young, and...

218
00:16:13,938 --> 00:16:15,872
Prosecutor Cha Si Young.

219
00:16:18,138 --> 00:16:21,305
You ran into Ji Won at the courthouse?

220
00:16:22,038 --> 00:16:25,372
Ji Won told me something interesting.

221
00:16:25,372 --> 00:16:30,038
In Lee Yong Woo's statement about Hye Jin,
the essential 'who' part is not there.

222
00:16:30,038 --> 00:16:33,938
He saw someone digging up
and moving the girl he killed,

223
00:16:33,938 --> 00:16:35,838
but never saw the face.

224
00:16:35,838 --> 00:16:37,505
And the flaw
in Professor Kang's statement is...

225
00:16:37,505 --> 00:16:39,238
That he didn't see it himself.

226
00:16:39,238 --> 00:16:40,338
Because he just heard it from someone else.

227
00:16:40,338 --> 00:16:41,672
Yes, that's right.

228
00:16:41,672 --> 00:16:44,172
Each of these testimonies alone is useless.

229
00:16:44,172 --> 00:16:46,638
They only gain credibility when combined.

230
00:16:46,638 --> 00:16:51,472
So what I saw and what you heard
must be combined

231
00:16:51,472 --> 00:16:53,638
for the testimony to carry weight?

232
00:16:53,638 --> 00:16:55,738
That's exactly it.

233
00:16:55,738 --> 00:17:00,272
Your testimony alone isn't enough to claim
the police covered up Hye Jin's case.

234
00:17:00,272 --> 00:17:04,138
But if we combine that
with what I heard 30 years ago...

235
00:17:04,138 --> 00:17:09,105
We can argue that they were police officers.

236
00:17:09,105 --> 00:17:12,472
So the headline for this report will be

237
00:17:12,472 --> 00:17:15,538
"Collaboration Between
a Serial Killer and a Profiler."

238
00:17:15,538 --> 00:17:17,738
You and I

239
00:17:17,738 --> 00:17:19,938
collaborate?

240
00:17:21,972 --> 00:17:23,572
Yeah.

241
00:17:24,238 --> 00:17:26,672
We are joining forces.

242
00:17:29,105 --> 00:17:30,738
We are?

243
00:17:34,838 --> 00:17:36,681
<i>Ji Won</i>

244
00:17:36,681 --> 00:17:38,705
<i>wants to meet you.</i>

245
00:17:48,038 --> 00:17:50,905
I can't say I'm happy to see you.

246
00:17:50,905 --> 00:17:52,705
You understand, right?

247
00:17:52,705 --> 00:17:55,605
What can I even say?

248
00:17:55,605 --> 00:17:58,338
I'm just grateful you came to see me.

249
00:18:00,505 --> 00:18:05,238
By the way, Ji Won,
you really haven't changed.

250
00:18:05,238 --> 00:18:09,738
I'd recognize you
the instant I saw you on the street.

251
00:18:10,472 --> 00:18:13,772
But we'll never pass
each other on the street again, will we?

252
00:18:17,705 --> 00:18:19,605
Oh, right.

253
00:18:22,172 --> 00:18:25,072
I have a lot to ask you,

254
00:18:26,205 --> 00:18:30,305
