707
00:51:58,605 --> 00:52:00,405
What?

708
00:52:02,638 --> 00:52:05,372
It looks like things are going
to get noisy again for a while.

709
00:52:06,572 --> 00:52:08,405
When are you coming back?

710
00:52:09,172 --> 00:52:11,038
That depends on you.

711
00:52:11,038 --> 00:52:13,305
Clean this up quick, okay?

712
00:52:13,305 --> 00:52:15,872
Darn it, maybe it's because
I'm getting older.

713
00:52:17,072 --> 00:52:23,705
I'm sick of foreign food now!
I'm sick of you, you rascal.

714
00:52:23,705 --> 00:52:25,353
[The prosecution and police
also apologize to Mr. Im]

715
00:52:31,273 --> 00:52:33,833
[Myeongjin University]

716
00:52:33,833 --> 00:52:36,005
[I can no longer believe
the professor's once righteous voice]

717
00:52:36,005 --> 00:52:38,405
[Who is truly evil? The professor, or them?]

718
00:52:38,405 --> 00:52:40,393
[The one who pursued truth
has become the center of lies]

719
00:52:44,172 --> 00:52:45,772
Mr. Cha.

720
00:52:46,772 --> 00:52:50,272
Just leave it. It'll pile up anyway.

721
00:52:50,272 --> 00:52:51,872
Just leave it.

722
00:52:53,005 --> 00:52:55,838
Anyway, what brings you here?

723
00:52:56,772 --> 00:52:58,872
Don't you feel wronged at all?

724
00:52:58,872 --> 00:53:01,205
You weren't the perpetrator, Professor.

725
00:53:04,372 --> 00:53:06,372
I was one too.

726
