757
00:54:57,505 --> 00:54:59,738
Well, if that's the reason, I could insist...

758
00:54:59,738 --> 00:55:01,372
No,

759
00:55:02,272 --> 00:55:04,238
there's no need for that anymore.

760
00:55:09,972 --> 00:55:12,372
So I'm no longer needed?

761
00:55:14,238 --> 00:55:18,738
What, now that you got
what you wanted, it's all over?

762
00:55:20,072 --> 00:55:21,705
No.

763
00:55:22,938 --> 00:55:25,338
Unfortunately, this still isn't over.

764
00:55:25,338 --> 00:55:27,505
No indictment?

765
00:55:27,505 --> 00:55:29,105
Why?

766
00:55:29,105 --> 00:55:32,172
Because the statute of limitations expired.

767
00:55:32,172 --> 00:55:34,905
What statute of limitations?
They're police officers!

768
00:55:34,905 --> 00:55:37,105
They're the ones who covered it up!

769
00:55:37,938 --> 00:55:42,005
So they're just going to neglect their duty
all the way until retirement, huh?

770
00:55:42,005 --> 00:55:45,938
Father, please calm down first.

771
00:55:47,138 --> 00:55:51,738
<i>None of those responsible for Hye Jin's case
were punished.</i>

772
00:55:51,738 --> 00:55:53,738
It's so unjust.

773
00:55:53,738 --> 00:55:56,105
- <i>If I keep fighting to the end,</i>
- That's not fair!

774
00:55:56,105 --> 00:55:58,372
<i>if I don't stop,</i>

775
00:55:58,372 --> 00:56:00,838
<i>then even if I lose,
I haven't truly been defeated.</i>

776
00:56:00,838 --> 00:56:03,638
Why go that far?

777
00:56:03,638 --> 00:56:06,105
It's not like the world
will change because of it.

778
00:56:06,105 --> 00:56:08,372
Back then,

779
00:56:09,372 --> 00:56:12,938
when I chased after you, the scarecrow,

780
00:56:13,705 --> 00:56:16,305
I realized I had become one myself.

781
00:56:20,472 --> 00:56:24,572
You, me, and them,

782
00:56:24,572 --> 00:56:26,872
we were all scarecrows.

783
00:56:29,838 --> 00:56:33,738
Now, I'm finally coming to my senses
and trying to act like a human.

784
00:56:34,905 --> 00:56:37,105
Scarecrows?

785
00:56:37,105 --> 00:56:39,605
We are different.

786
00:56:39,605 --> 00:56:42,538
We uncovered the truth!

787
00:56:45,338 --> 00:56:49,238
Don't ever think you did the right thing.

788
00:56:51,838 --> 00:56:55,138
Because you were
the beginning of all this tragedy.

789
00:57:09,338 --> 00:57:11,938
Never forget that

790
00:57:12,872 --> 00:57:14,605
for the rest of your life.

791
00:57:29,238 --> 00:57:30,872
Tae Joo!

792
00:57:33,738 --> 00:57:35,372
Could you...

793
00:57:36,772 --> 00:57:39,772
come see me someday?

794
00:57:41,872 --> 00:57:43,838
Not as a profiler...

795
00:57:46,172 --> 00:57:48,172
but as a friend.

796
00:57:54,238 --> 00:57:56,372
If...

797
00:57:56,372 --> 00:57:58,238
just if,

798
00:57:59,205 --> 00:58:03,905
the day ever comes when you
truly repent for what you've done,

799
00:58:06,572 --> 00:58:08,538
then I'll think about it.

800
00:58:11,405 --> 00:58:13,305
Once you've

801
00:58:14,272 --> 00:58:16,905
set the whole world right as you wish,

802
00:58:18,857 --> 00:58:20,638
I hope

803
00:58:20,638 --> 00:58:23,038
you'll tell me about it someday.

804
00:58:25,072 --> 00:58:27,872
Tell me how this story ends.

805
00:58:55,938 --> 00:58:57,545
Today

806
00:58:57,545 --> 00:59:01,038
is your last profiling session, sir.

807
00:59:01,038 --> 00:59:03,438
Thank you for all your hard work.

808
00:59:09,972 --> 00:59:11,252
I remember

809
00:59:11,252 --> 00:59:14,405
the first time I came here.

810
00:59:15,072 --> 00:59:16,649
Back then,

811
00:59:16,649 --> 00:59:19,572
this place felt like an endless maze.

812
00:59:23,505 --> 00:59:26,038
[Visitation Room 1]

813
00:59:26,705 --> 00:59:29,172
I wonder if I'll ever come back here again.

814
00:59:31,753 --> 00:59:33,396
Well...

815
00:59:34,838 --> 00:59:36,905
I hope I can.

816
00:59:40,038 --> 00:59:42,438
Good work, Officer Lee.

817
00:59:55,505 --> 00:59:59,038
<i>I had a dream.</i>

818
01:00:02,338 --> 01:00:04,638
<i>You know, about one of those days,</i>

819
01:00:05,405 --> 01:00:08,572
<i>the kind that everyone probably has</i>

820
01:00:09,238 --> 01:00:10,972
<i>at least once.</i>

821
01:00:12,505 --> 01:00:13,805
Where have you been?

822
01:00:13,805 --> 01:00:16,205
Is it really that hard
to come early and help?

823
01:00:16,205 --> 01:00:17,505
All the guests have arrived already.

824
01:00:17,505 --> 01:00:18,538
Come on, think about it.

825
01:00:18,538 --> 01:00:21,472
You think I can just
leave criminals be for a baby's birthday?

826
01:00:21,472 --> 01:00:24,405
Of course you'd come, you're his only uncle.

827
01:00:24,405 --> 01:00:26,772
Hurry up and greet the guests.

828
01:00:29,372 --> 01:00:32,938
Come on, the kid won't even remember
any of this. Why make such a huge fuss?

829
01:00:33,705 --> 01:00:35,472
<i>So,</i>

830
01:00:35,472 --> 01:00:37,257
<i>a day that</i>

831
01:00:37,257 --> 01:00:39,805
<i>probably wouldn't remain</i>

832
01:00:39,805 --> 01:00:41,638
<i>in anyone's memory years later.</i>

833
01:00:47,105 --> 01:00:49,305
Why is he here?

834
01:01:17,005 --> 01:01:19,072
<i>That's when I realized.</i>

835
01:01:20,805 --> 01:01:23,405
<i>For those of us</i>

836
01:01:25,238 --> 01:01:27,938
<i>who lived through Kangseng in 1988,</i>

837
01:01:30,038 --> 01:01:32,838
<i>it was a kind of day we never got to enjoy.</i>

838
01:01:47,938 --> 01:01:49,513
<i>The kind of day</i>

839
01:01:49,513 --> 01:01:51,972
<i>we longed for</i>

840
01:01:53,572 --> 01:01:55,705
<i>with all our hearts.</i>

841
01:01:58,672 --> 01:02:01,905
<i>The people I couldn't protect,</i>

842
01:02:05,738 --> 01:02:07,372
<i>my hometown,</i>

843
01:02:13,305 --> 01:02:16,238
<i>and all my memories were there.</i>

844
01:02:29,505 --> 01:02:31,505
Hey, I told you to stop hitting my head.

845
01:02:31,505 --> 01:02:34,838
How could you show up late
at your own nephew's first birthday party?

846
01:02:37,138 --> 01:02:38,805
Happy now?

847
01:02:38,805 --> 01:02:40,405
Of course.

848
01:02:59,238 --> 01:03:01,372
I didn't want to wake up.

849
01:03:03,572 --> 01:03:06,872
Seriously? I hit your head first
even in your dreams?

850
01:03:06,872 --> 01:03:08,805
What kind of dream is that?

851
01:03:09,738 --> 01:03:11,205
Guess I really missed it.

852
01:03:11,205 --> 01:03:14,372
You used to smack my head every now and then.

853
01:03:14,372 --> 01:03:16,372
Don't worry.

854
01:03:16,372 --> 01:03:18,105
I'm gonna make up

855
01:03:18,105 --> 01:03:21,638
for the last thirty years and smack
that thick head of yours nice and slow.

856
01:03:21,638 --> 01:03:23,238
Sounds good.

857
01:03:25,972 --> 01:03:28,138
Jeez, I'm jealous.

858
01:03:29,272 --> 01:03:32,172
I wish I could have a dream like that too.

859
01:03:33,072 --> 01:03:35,497
If none of that

860
01:03:35,497 --> 01:03:37,172
had happened in Kangseng,

861
01:03:37,172 --> 01:03:41,272
what kind of lives would we have lived?

862
01:03:41,272 --> 01:03:42,905
At the very least,

863
01:03:43,838 --> 01:03:45,472
everyone

864
01:03:49,505 --> 01:03:51,605
would've been together.

